An Act relating to public finance; directing the
Office of Management and Enterprise Services (OMES)
to create reporting function to assess whether
contract is service-driven or for staff augmentation;
directing OMES to amend state accounting manual;
requiring permanent file location for invoices for
intangible assets; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
SUBJECT: Public finance
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 34.11.11 of Title 62, unless
there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
A. The Office of Management and Enterprise Services (OMES)
shall create a reporting function within the state's accounting
software to assess whether a contract is service-driven or for staff
augmentation.
B. OMES shall amend the state accounting manual to require that
any invoice for intangible assets include a file path to a permanent
file location where the asset will be maintained during post-review.
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.

Passed the House of Representatives the 24th day of March, 2026.
Presiding Officer of the House
of Representatives
Passed the Senate the 28th day of April, 2026.
